titleInfo.title: USA v. Stelly
titleInfo.subTitle: JUDGMENT for Revocation of Probation or Supervised Release as to Malik M. Stelly (1), - Defendant admitted guilt to violation of the mandatory condition which states the defendant shall not commit another federal, state or local crime during of the term of supervision ; defendant shall enter and participate in a community confinement program, in the community corrections component with work release for a period of 120 days or until discharged by the United States Probation Office pursuant to 18 U.S.S.G. 3563(b)(11); defendant's current term of supervised release of three (3) years shall continue and is scheduled to complete February 14, 2010; $100 special assessment has been paid in full as to defendant(s) Malik M. Stelly. Allegations 2 and 3 of the petition dismissed on the motion of the United States as to this defendant only. The defendant is remanded to the custody of the United States Marshal pending placement in a community confinement program. Ordered by Chief Judge Joseph F. Bataillon. (4 Certified copies to USM)(ADB, )
